	"description": "&gt; 3. 7. 2018: UPDATED to ReasonReact v0.4.2\nYou may have heard of Reason [https://reasonml.github.io/] before. It’s a syntax\non top of OCaml [https://ocaml.org/] that compiles to both readable JavaScript\ncode and to native and bytecode as well.\n\nThis means you could potentially write a single application\n[https://github.com/jaredly/gravitron]using Reason syntax, and be able to run it\nin the browser, and on Android and iOS phones as well.\n\nThis is one of the reasons why Reason (ouch, pun) is beco",
